<H2>Further Information</H2>

<p>An acknowledgment of the ISCCP resources is appreciated if you are 
publishing any scientific materials using any of the data and/or products 
found in this website or ordered through any of our data archive centers. 
The following are samples of acknowledgment statements.</p>

<div style="padding-left:16px">
<p>
The ISCCP D2 data/images were obtained from the International Satellite Cloud Climatology Project
web site https://isccp.giss.nasa.gov maintained by the ISCCP research group at the
NASA Goddard Institute for Space Studies, New York, NY on [date]. 
Rossow, W.B., and R.A. Schiffer, 1999:
Advances in understanding clouds from ISCCP.
<cite>Bull. Amer. Meteorol. Soc.</cite>, <b>80</b>, 2261-2288.
</p>

<p>The ISCCP DX data were obtained from the International Satellite Cloud Climatology Project
data archives at
<!-- Langley Research Center (LaRC) http://eosweb.larc.nasa.gov EOS DAAC on [date]. --> 
NOAA/NESDIS/NCDC Satellite Services Group, ncdc.satorder@noaa.gov, on [date].
Rossow, W.B., and R.A. Schiffer, 1999:
Advances in understanding clouds from ISCCP.
<cite>Bull. Amer. Meteorol. Soc.</cite>, <b>80</b>, 2261-2288.
</p>


</div>


<p>Also note that you should reference the ISCCP project and/or data product descriptions 
as appropriate.</p>


<div style="padding-left:16px">

<p><i>ISCCP Project:</i><br>
Schiffer, R.A., and W.B. Rossow, 1983:
<a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/sc01000b.html">The International Satellite Cloud Climatology Project (ISCCP): The first project of the World Climate Research Programme</a>.
<cite>Bull. Amer. Meteorol. Soc.</cite>, <b>64</b>, 779-784.</p>

<p><i>ISCCP B3 Radiance Data Set:</i><br>
Schiffer, R.A., and W.B. Rossow, 1985:
<a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/sc02000x.html">ISCCP global radiance data set: A new resource for climate research</a>.
<cite>Bull. Amer. Meteorol. Soc.</cite>, <b>66</b>, 1498-1505,
doi:10.1175/1520-0477(1985)066&lt;1498:IGRDSA&gt;2.0.CO;2.</p>

<p><i>ISCCP Cloud Data Products:</i><br>
Rossow, W.B., and R.A. Schiffer, 1999:
<a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/ro04100j.html">Advances in understanding clouds from ISCCP</a>.
<cite>Bull. Amer. Meteorol. Soc.</cite>, <b>80</b>, 2261-2288,
doi:10.1175/1520-0477(1999)080&lt;2261:AIUCFI&gt;2.0.CO;2.</p>

</div>



